Product name: Neiger Brothers Czech Glass Egyptian Revival-Late 1920's-.75"
Description:
This is a fantastic pair of Egyptian Revival earrings made between 1920 and 1935 and designed by Max and Norbert Neiger. These earring are composed of Czechoslovakian pressed turquoise glass which is prong set into a Victorian brass base with floral detail typical to the period. Originally these earrings would have been screw backs but the backs were removed sometime in the 1960's and replaced with 14k post backs(see pictures). The earrings measure.75" and show wear(loss of paint) typical to age.
The story behind Neiger Jewelry is so interesting and inspiring. It is obvious why these designs command such high prices, it is not just the designs but the history of the work.  
Max and Norbert Neiger were two Czech brothers who made wonderful jewelry with figural glass components in Gablonz, Czechoslovakia, in from 1905 to the 1930s. As the Germans advanced near Gablonz in 1939, the two Jewish brothers left their factory and escaped to Bohemia, where they continued to produce jewelry in a scaled-down operation. They were later arrested in Prague and, in 1942, were exterminated by the Nazis at Auschwitz.
Please review the photos carefully and email with any questions you may have prior to making a purchase.
Enjoy🌞

Product name: Mid-century Modernist Karl Gustav Hansen, Hans Hansen, Denmark. Leaf brooch sterling silver.
Description:
Oxidiced, solid sterling silver, leaf brooch. Karl Gustav Hansen, Hans Hansen, Kolding, Denmark.
Marks: Hans Hansen  925 S Denmark 134
Measures: 7,8 X 1,5 cm. Weight: c. 12 grams. Roll-over safety clasp.
Clean and simple modernist design. 
Very good condition, with light signs of wear. Tarnished. The pin at the back is slightly bent. No damage.
Hans Hansen (1884-1940) opened a goldsmith shop and smithy in Kolding, Denmark, around 1906. Initially the company produced flatware. Once that was successful, they started producing jewelry. 
The first pieces were designed by Hansen himself around 1931, but the production of jewelry really began in 1932, with a collection designed by Hansen's son Karl Gustav Hansen (born 1914). 
Karl Gustav took over the Hans Hansen Silver-smithy when his father died in 1940. The company Hans Hansen became one of the most prominent silver-smithies in Denmark. In 1992 the firm joined with the Georg Jensen company. (Main source: Jensensilver.com).

Product name: Sale -  Hakama - Pants Style - Vintage Japanese Hakama Brown or Gray
Description:
Make a fashion statement! These pleated pants are typically worn by Japanese men for formal occasions.
Deep side slits make them "one size fits most" with length typically range from 32 - 34" (that's the outseam (hip to heel), not the inseam!) and are traditionally worn low on the hips. If these are not long enough for you, you can request a custom made hakama.
Colors are limited to dark browns and medium to dark gray and solid and striped versions of each color.  Photos are examples of typical colors - yours will be slightly different.   We very occasionally have other dark colors (green, blue, black or other striped versions) - feel free to inquire before ordering.
The fabric is mostly silk, though the finish might be satiny or a crisp silk, or occasionally a nubby raw silk.  If you have a preference for this, please let us know by convo when you order and we'll do the best we can when we choose from the several dozen we have in stock at any time.
This listing is for the pants style, with a divided pantleg and a low crotch - near the knee. If you wear a kimono underneath them, you must raise the kimono length with a fold at the waist under a sash. Or you could try the skirt style, which we list separately.

Product name: Doctor Bag - Gladstone Bag - Antique French Leather Doctors Handbag - Vintage Boho Handbag - Medical Bag
Description:
I saw this doctors bag at a Vide Grenier (like an English "car boot" sale or an American "garage sale") in the nearby village of Maillezais. The vendor, an octogenarian Madame, informed me it had been her late grandfather's working bag and she proudly proclaimed that many a malaise had been cured by its contents being sagely administered by him whilst "on his rounds".
It is made of leather, opens and closes easily, and  apart from the catch there are also  two sliding brass plates on either side of the handle which act as locking devices should one wish to ensure the security of the bags contents whilst walking about, as inevitably a doctor would. Its interior is fabric lined and in the condition one would anticipate of a bag with more than a century of usage.

Description:
What. A. Statement. 
This gorgeous Bellini hat screams 1960s. It's a heavy wool felt in a bold, deep green with an equally bold mustard yellow trim. The interior stamp reads "Doeskin Felt - 100% wool - Made in USA - Bollman Hat Co." The label reads "Bellini - New York." 
The hat features a wide upturned brim with a medium-size crown. It's all in very good vintage condition - I found two spots on the underside of the brim where there's some dried glue residue (photo 5), but other than that, I can't find a thing wrong with it. It's also very heavy, and the bow makes it lopsided - you'll definitely need to anchor it in place! 
On the right is a large matching bow with rhinestones down both sides of the center - no missing stones, and they're all held in with prongs. Did I say large? The bow itself is 10" long and 6" wide at the ends. 
Measurements:  14" from front to back, and 13" wide. It measures 21" in circumference at the grosgrain ribbon - BUT, it fits MUCH larger than that. Most 21" hats fit me okay, but this one is way too big. If you wear more of a size 23 or even a 24, this is probably closer to your size. The crown is 4.5" tall; the brim is 3.5" wide.

Product name: the SoulSpace Oracle deck
Description:
This 60-card oracle deck is adorned with prints of luscious, intuitive, watercolor paintings embellished with white and black ink, each offering a soulful word for contemplation. The backs of all cards show a gentle, warm, pastel watercolor wash, visible in the last two photos in this listing. The 61st card in the deck is simply a title card, as seen in the photos above. 
All cards are packaged together in a convenient custom-printed, shrink-wrapped box for safe-keeping, which also details ideas for ways the cards can be used. The front and back of box can be seen in photos in the listing. All art was made by me, Jen Berlingo. 
These cards are "tarot sized" or 2.75" x 4.75" and are printed upon the finest quality, smooth, non-glossy, German card stock with black core to prevent transparency. 
Select cards from this deck are printed onto greeting cards. If you'd like to check out the art work in more detail, see the greeting card listings:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/472638736/numinous-greetings-set-of-6-cards
and
https://www.etsy.com/listing/472636506/humanness-greetings-set-of-6-cards
You can also see many images of this deck in Instagram under the hashtag #SoulSpaceOracle -- share your images there using this hashtag, too! 
Answer to the most common FAQ: 
In Spring 2016, I sold the original SoulSpace Oracle deck on Etsy, which only contained 30 cards. This deck includes all 30 of the original cards PLUS 30 additional cards, for a complete 60 card deck. 
GIFTS:
If you're purchasing this as a gift for a loved one and want it shipped directly to them, please enter their address in the shipping field, and indicate in the "Notes to Seller" that it's a gift, and a gift message for me to pass along. 
*   *   *   *   *   *   *   *   *   *   
Ideas for using your SoulSpace Oracle deck:
If you’re seeking a quick, fun, and meaningful way to look inward, working with oracle cards could be an enriching practice for you. The simple act of choosing a card (or a few cards) is an immediate way to invite self-reflection, whether you are starting your day, seeking insight into a lingering question, or invoking nighttime dreams. In meditating upon the image and message of the cards you draw, meaning arises your insights, associations, and inner wisdom. You don’t need to be a professional tarot reader, a shaman, a believer of woo-woo, or anything other than exactly who you are to make oracle cards part of your practice. 
Times you might consider drawing a card:
• At the start of your morning
• To set intentions for your day or week, placed upon an altar or around the house as visual reminders
• As creative writing or journaling prompts
• For help in answering a question you're pondering
• Before bedtime, to close your day or invoke/inquire into your nighttime dreams
• To mark special occasions, like your birthday, new years, or the beginning of a project
• To mark a transition, like a move, a new job, a birth, a death, a relationship beginning or ending
• If you're a healing arts practitioner, teacher, advisor, or work alongside others in any capacity, consider keeping SoulSpace Oracle cards on your desk to invite clients or coworkers to pull a card at the begining of a session or meeting to arrive into the sacred space and set the tone for the session
Prompts you can use when pulling SoulSpace Oracle cards:
Drawing 1 card, you might ask for insight around a particular topic, or "What energy do I need to bring into the day ahead?"
Drawing 3 cards, you might ask one of these sets of questions:
• Who was I? Who am I? Who will I become?
• Where was I? Where am I? Where am I going?
• What am I keeping private? What am I showing to others? How are others
seeing me?
• What am I heading toward? What is in my way? What tool can I use to
overcome that obstacle?
Other uses for your SoulSpace Oracle deck:
• Tape an inspirational word to your bathroom mirror, computer, or car dashboard
• Send good vibes to a friend by finding a fitting card and writing a note on the pastel card backing
• Leave a card for a stranger under their windshield wiper or near the cream & sugar at your favorite cafe
I hope the SoulSpace oracle brings you joy and light. xo, Jen

That's great, but I go one step further!  By running each piece through a thickness planer (on all four faces), the pieces are much closer to uniform thickness which is key to game play.  It's still wood and the pieces aren't perfect and they may expand with moisture in the air, but this significantly reduces the variation.
This game consists of 54 individually hand cut pieces of wood.  I used 2x3's and ran them through a planer and then a sander so they would be smooth enough for game play.  Each piece is 7.5" long and the tower is 27" when game play begins.  Then the height grows from there when game play begins!  
The carrying tote can be added to your order for an additional fee.  The standard price includes a tote with the Texan Rustic Elements logo.  You can also select the upgraded tote which can include a custom message or image.
Thanks for checking out my listing and have fun playing the game!
<How to Play 
The game is typically played with 2 or more players.  First build the tower stacking the pieces as carefully as possible.  Then take turns removing a block (using only one hand) and place on the top. The object of the game is to be the last player to successfully stack a wooden block without knocking over the tower.

Product name: Electric Guitar Pickup : FlatCat™ Surface Mounted for Standard and Cigar Box Guitars
Description:
FREE SHIPPING within mainland U.S. 
Demo videos listed at end of this section. 
"I finally finished the guitar for which I bought your pickups and have had several players over to try it.  Everyone agrees your pickups sound great.  They lived up to every claim you make and then some :D"
   -- R. Duke
"I LOVE THESE PICKUPS!  They sound amazing!! I just tried the new 4th gen full size pickups and they really crank it out!!  THANKS SO MUCH." 
   -- Rocket Instruments
Add controls to your set:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/467981068/pre-wired-guitar-controls
WHAT ARE FLATCATS?
FlatCat's are no-hum, noise-free, full-power guitar pickups... but they're only 1/4" thick and are mounted on the surface of your guitar.  Easy-to-understand installation instructions are included with the pickup.  
FlatCats work with standard electric guitars, cigar box guitars (CBGs), folk guitars and other instruments that use steel- or nickel-core strings.  They produce especially fine tone and sound range.
FEATURES:
* Unique design eliminates pickup-generated hum and noise
* Only 1/4" thick but all the power of a full-size pickup
* Mounts on the surface of your guitar-- no major routing required
* Entire pickup body sits right under the strings, pulling in every bit of sound
* Full-bodied, unique, rich sound with a variety of range
* Available in several sizes to and colors meet your needs
* Fully hand-made custom pickup  
* Customers love it
WHY ARE FLATCATS SPECIAL?
Most pickups are largely buried in the guitar body-- with the primary magnetic field a distance away from the strings. But the entire FlatCat sits right under the strings with the active field totally surrounding both strings and pickup. This produces an accurate, vibrant, rich sound that can't be gained from standard pickups.  
FlatCats are very versatile pickups-- with sounds ranging from mellow blues to ROCK OUT!  They are priced surprisingly low for a  custom hand-made pickup.  Check out my store's Reviews section to see what others say about FlatCats (they're all actual customer reviews, no "plants").   Try one-- or two as a matched set.  The sound is simply awesome.
SOME CUSTOMER REVIEWS ON ETSY:
"Fantastic pickup with impeccable design and craftsmanship. Sounds great and is thin enough to surface mount on all the types of guitars I build."
"This is the second one that I have bought. Excellent output & tone for a flat PU. Great installation, easy."
"This flat pickup is thin, quiet, and outputs whatever the strings are doing. The resin-potted design is a decided advancement over the use of wax in pickups. This was my first order of a FlatCat-It will not be my last!"
Demo video links are at the bottom of this description area.
UNIQUE SIZE, UNIQUE SOUND
A professional luthier stated: "This has such a balanced sound. It brings out a full bass end without losing the trebles, and has almost an acoustic sub-tone to it.  It's a great pickup."  
FlatCat provides a complete balance between the bass and treble strings. On some guitars you pluck the low E string and it just rumbles, and the trebles are faded out or tinny.  FlatCat brings out all of the strings evenly, applying proper bass to the wound strings and volume to the trebles without sounding tinny in the process.  The result is a harmonious balance between all strings.
Moderate the volume and tone and you have the mellowest of blues.  Crank the volume and FlatCat can really romp.  
TOTALLY HAND-MADE
Each FlatCat™ is individually hand-made with great care.  The pickup is potted and encased in solid PolyResin (incredibly tough stuff).  The proprietary FlatCat design eliminates the hum you get from single pickups.  
The FlatCat is surface-mounted to your instrument. Rather than needing to route or carve a hollow for your pickup, all you need to do is mount it directly over the existing pickup hollow or drill a small hole for the wire. You can even add one to a single-pickup electric guitar without having to re-route the body.  Full instructions are included for multiple mounting techniques.
MAKE IT YOUR OWN
FlatCats come in several colors, or can be painted and decorated to your preference.  The body is made from sturdy poly-resin, presenting an excellent canvas for your own personal touch.  (Choose one of the "primers" at ordering time for a "do it yourself" finish.)
Gold Foil is a laser-etched 24k gold finish.
Color Chart note:   The colors shown are actual photos of our finishes.   Individual pickups may vary in appearance. 
SIZE DIMENSIONS:
FlatCats are approximately 1/4" thick.  The available styles are:
* CBG (Cigar Box Guitar).   2" x 2"
* FULL SIZE:  3 3/4" x 1 7/8".  Same size as standard humbucker with a mounting ring. 
* SPLIT BASS PAIR:   two 2"x2" pickups designed to focus on 2 or 3 strings each.
You can use one, two or three FlatCats together... or add one to your existing pickups  (Please add a comment to your order if you're using them as a set so that I can configure them for you.)
Stratocaster note:   FlatCats can be mounted on the neck or mid position of a Stratocaster.  
*** FREE SHIPPING within the primary U.S. on all FlatCat orders. ***
VIDEO DEMOS of the FlatCat™:
https://youtu.be/5LfWT0pNY7I  
ElectraGlide CBG-- demo at 50 sec.  An archival video of a FlatCat prototype-- with a bit of built in growl!
https://youtu.be/aEeoZXhPxzM  
The unique "Altoids Mintar"
https://youtu.be/VCeB5uvx2j8 
Hazardous Voltage CBG-- demo at 25 sec
https://youtu.be/j-Mk_f-fsmQ 
Four Aces CBG-- demo at 30 sec
https://youtu.be/guQxYW7ED7U   
FlatCats on the Red Wine Multi-Voice guitar
And check out this special demo at Rocket Instruments!
www.rocketsinstruments.com
INSTALLATION
FlatCats are usually installed using either double-sided tape (included) or a dab of silicone glue at each corner.  Other easy-to-follow methods are included in the full installation instructions.  You can usually simply remove the current pickup and connect your FlatCat to the existing wires, or if not replacing an existing pickup just drill a small hole or two for the wires.  FlatCats are generally far easier to install than standard pickups.  
If you have any questions, please feel free to contact me here and I will be happy to assist you in ordering the correct FlatCat for your needs.  
FlatCat is a Trademark of Wishbringer Hand-Crafted Instruments.  All rights reserved.
Stratocaster is TM Fender and is used here as reference.  No affiliation is implied.

The Unity Sand Ceremony is becoming on of the most popular additions to the Traditional Wedding Ceremony.  The side containers are filled with sand of your choice, 2 colors which compliment each other or match the colors of your Wedding decor.  Some people use real sand from beaches which are meaningful to them.  Many possibilities!  During the Wedding Ceremony, the Bride and Groom will lift the side containers, which represent the individual, and pour the sand into the center container which is symbolic of blending their 2 lives together. With this listing - Children would be included in the Blending of Sand to symbolize Family Unity.  Each individual would choose a different colored sand for the ceremony.

Also the names of children involved in ceremony both on side cases and on center container! Colors of the lettering can be changed as can the saying if you prefer!   Additional side vases may be purchased as well if you plan to have more than 4 people pouring sand in your Family Blended Sand Ceremony. As shown, this set would be center block  6

Product name: Glassblowing Swivel -Stainless Steel 90 degree Double Swivel - 1/4 inch OR 3/8 inch
Description:
1/4" swivels are now VERSION 2- 55% Larger Bore Airway than Original Version (not yet pictured!)
These are the double sided, Stainless Steel swivels everyone (ok.. mostly glassblowers) have been talking about!   Made in USA, Rochester, MN.
  304 Stainless- will not rust under normal use.  Don't put them in bleach, strong acid, or, I've been told, blood.  (304 is a slightly magnetic stainless, but don't expect to be able to hold your swivel up with a magnet)  This also means the swivel is lightweight.
  Double Sided- 2 swivels in one.  Straight swivels will last twice as long.  If one side does bind up, you have the chance to see that happen, and to catch it, since the other side will be spinning.
  At the bench, since both legs of the 90° swivel, you won't experience torque as you move your piece from one hand to the other..  or whatever position you put your work into.
  The 3/8ths inch swivels are generally used on lathes or offhand, due to their larger size and weight.  They allow for greater airflow, and can alleviate some back-pressure problems encountered with larger vessels.
  These have received Rave reviews from lampworkers around the World:
On the American Scientific Glassblowers Society Facebook page:
http://tinyurl.com/lnxd2d4
  On TalkGlass.com:
http://tinyurl.com/m9ldxsf
  If you do not like it, return it within 30 days, for a refund of the purchase price, minus 6.10 shipping.
  These are the same great swivels that Blastshield is carrying.  I am the sole supplier of these swivels.
  CARE instructions:  clean with soap and water every 3-6 months, and immediately lubricate with lightweight oil.  3 in 1 is fine.  This keeps the water from drying, and causing hard water buildup.  If your water is especially hard, wash with rubbing alcohol.  If you've gotten hard water buildup, try soaking the swivel overnight in vinegar.

Product name: Heishi Large Hole Bead Ocean Jasper approx. 44 Big Hole Beads For Leather
Description:
Large hole Ocean Jasper Heishi beads are dressed in rich earth tones with big holes of  2 and 1/2 mm. Use for 2mm leather and other cords and laces. Heishi's are 10mm and are natural gemstone beads. Each strand, as well as each bead will be unique. Please except some natural pitting which is  normal  for Ocean Jasper.
You will receive a 7.5 -8". strand of approx 40-45 beads. If you need  more than what is listed, 
please contact me  before you check out for availability and reserved listing.
IMPORTANT NOTE... The only known Ocean jasper mine in the world is mined out and now closed. The rough that is being cut now is what is left from what had been previously mined and is what is left. As they mined the lower levels the rough became less colorful. Whether or not more of these beads will available and how colorful they will be I don't know. My stock is getting quite low. Once the rough that has already been mined is gone there will be no more new product. I have been hearing this for about a year now and every bit of info I have been able to gather leads me to believe that this is true.
 What I have in now Feb..2017 look very much like the picture.
NOTE:
With the exception of a few, my big hole beads have holes that are approx 2 mm - 4 mm. They  are not huge hole beads like Pandora beads. My big hole beads are meant to fit comfortably on 2-4 mm leather. Please read the listing carefully.  Example..A  big hole bead with a 2 mm hole will not fit over over a 3 mm cord. The only exception  is some 3-5 mm soft flat thin laces may be able to be worked through a smaller hole. If you have questions contact me before purchasing.
 Folk Lore says:
Ocean jasper is the stone of high spirits and joy. It opens one's awareness to the benevolent aspects of life and lifts one's mood through its positive vibrations. It helps one to overcome feelings of sorrow, fear and worry and comforts and calms. It encourages the love of oneself and of others. It is a stone that aids with emotions and brings a sense of peace which helps us connect to nature and the earth.

Product name: Portugal Antique Azulejo Tile Replica Chandelier Earrings,  Ilhavo - Dove Frescoes from Sintra Palace Chapel - Persian Bohemian Boho Hippie
Description:
The city of Aveiro is known as the Venice of Portugal because of its canals and lovely hand painted and colorful boats called "moliceiros".
The city dates back to the 10th century when it was known by its first Latin name of Alavarium, literally, "a gathering place or preserve of birds." The Moors invaded and then held it until the 11th century, after which it became popular with Portuguese royalty. In the winter of 1575, a terrible storm closed the entrance to its port, ending a thriving trade in metals and tiles. The same storm also created a reef barrier at the Atlantic Ocean.
These tiles are located on the facade of a very, very old building in the lovely town of Ilhavo. To my dismay, many old buildings have fallen in disrepair and this is an attempt to preserve a little of the patrimony of Portugal before it's too late.
Deep in the misty mountains lies the enchanting city of Sintra, home to ancient castles, fairy-tale palaces, and verdant gardens. For centuries, sultans, kings, and wealthy noblemen were drawn by the area’s haunting beauty, and they left a trail of opulence and grandeur behind them.
These earrings are replicas of the Frescoes on the walls of the chapel at the National Palace of Sintra! Amazing! See photo!
The earrings are almost 8cm long (about 3" by 1 1/2" wide )and lightweight. Czech Glass Beads! 3 oz or 9 grams each
All my tiles are replicas made of polymer clay where the image actually becomes part of the clay through baking. No glue is used in the process. The pieces become waterproof and scratch resistant. Due to the handmade and hand shaped nature of each tile, slight variations will occur, as no two pieces are alike.
Wear a Piece of History!
Please feel free to email me with any questions you may have.
 Please note that some of our items will come with a tag stating "Return only accepted if tag is attached".  There are no exceptions to this policy.
Thank you,
Atrio

Soft soled boots are ideal for babies that are learning to walk, they are able to balance better because they can grip and spread their toes...giving them more control.
These Mukluks are Native American made, and would make a unique one of a kind baby gift...suitable as the next family heirloom.
FOR CUSTOM ORDERS: Please measure the length of your child's foot and add up to 1/4" to 1/2" (or 1.25 cm) to allow room for growth. This is your “Sole Length” in the chart below.
PLEASE ALLOW at least 1-2 weeks on custom orders. If there is not a backlog of orders it usually takes me 2-4 days to complete...(please contact me for a completion time).

LEATHER AVAILABILITY: Most deer hide bought and sold in the US are from the wild...meaning they are subject to injuries and scarring from thickets, brush, ticks etc. I order only the highest quality hides available...but even then there is no such thing as a perfect hide...there may be slight color variations and texture differences in every hide. I work around these as much as possible to offer you the best looking shoes I can. 
Because deer hides are seasonal...the availability can be limited at times. I have a few reliable suppliers that I work with...that offer the quality that I am looking for. However, because they buy from different tanneries, the coloring can vary. I try to keep the colors as close as possible to the shoe photos...but please when ordering your shoes...choose your leather color from the colors that are listed. The colors in the listings will show the color leather that is currently available to me. I will then make for you a quality shoe with only the highest level of craftsmanship. Thank you for your understanding.
